rse\" />"},"202":{"id":"/docs-8","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"<Card title=\"Stringify SDK\" description=\"Serialize AST nodes and build Markdown with typed primitives\" href=\"/docs/stringify\" />"},"203":{"id":"/docs-9","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"<Card title=\"Format SDK\" description=\"Define bidirectional formats with datamark()\" href=\"/docs/template\" />"},"204":{"id":"/docs-10","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"<Card title=\"Examples\" description=\"Real-world format definitions for common patterns\" href=\"/docs/examples\" />"},"205":{"id":"/docs-11","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why-datamark","content":"Markdown is the universal format for structured text, but parsing it into typed data usually means one of two things:"},"206":{"id":"/docs-12","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why-datamark","content":"**Regex and string manipulation** — fragile, unreadable, unmaintainable."},"207":{"id":"/docs-13","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why-datamark","content":"**Abstract syntax trees** — powerful, but you still write imperative traversal code."},"208":{"id":"/docs-14","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why-datamark","content":"datamark gives you a third option: **a unified AST with a native section tree** and **a lightweight format system** that makes common patterns trivial."},"209":{"id":"/docs-15","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#why-datamark","content":"**Bring your own validator.** datamark uses the Standard Schema v1 interface, so Zod, Valibot, ArkType, TypeBox, and any compliant library work out of the box."},"210":{"id":"/docs-16","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-datamark-is-not","content":"**It is not a static site generator.** It parses and transforms Markdown, but it does not build HTML pages or apply themes."},"211":{"id":"/docs-17","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-datamark-is-not","content":"**It is not a Markdown renderer.** It produces data, not HTML."},"212":{"id":"/docs-18","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-datamark-is-not","content":"**It does not stream.** Input string in, typed object out."},"213":{"id":"/docs-19","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-datamark-is-not","content":"**It is not a general-purpose parser generator.** It is specifically designed for Markdown documents."},"214":{"id":"/docs-20","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#who-is-it-for","content":"<Card title=\"CLI & Script Developers\" description=\"Parse READMEs, changelogs, plan files, and API docs into structured data for automation, validation, and CI.\" />"},"215":{"id":"/docs-21","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#who-is-it-for","content":"<Card title=\"Application Developers\" description=\"Embed typed Markdown parsing into your app for user-generated content, configuration files, and documentation formats.\" />"},"216":{"id":"/docs-22","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#quick-navigation","content":"Goal"},"217":{"id":"/docs-23","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#quick-navigation","content":"Section"},"218":{"id":"/docs-24","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#quick-navigation","content":"New here?"},"219":{"id":"/docs-25","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#quick-navigation","content":"Quickstart"},"220":{"id":"/docs-26","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#quick-navigation","content":"Understand the architecture"},"221":{"id":"/docs-27","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#quick-navigation","content":"The AST"},"222":{"id":"/docs-28","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#quick-navigation","content":"Look up a function"},"223":{"id":"/docs-29","p